# Database Schema - Note Sync Now

> **Status:** Active  
> **Created:** 2026-04-17  
> **Last Updated:** 2026-04-17

## Overview

This document defines the database schema for Note Sync Now's server-side persistence layer. The system supports both Redis and SQLite as storage backends.

## Schema (DBML Format)

```dbml
// Note Sync Now Database Schema
// Version: 1.0.0

// Rooms represent sync chains (identified by room ID derived from mnemonic)
Table rooms {
  id varchar [pk]           // Room ID (hash of mnemonic)
  created_at timestamp      // Room creation time
  updated_at timestamp      // Last update time
  expires_at timestamp      // Data expiration time (7 days TTL)
  encrypted_data text       // Encrypted room state
  version int               // Current version number
}

// Operations log tracks all sync operations for conflict detection
Table operations {
  id varchar [pk]           // Operation ID (UUID)
  room_id varchar [ref: > rooms.id]  // Reference to room
  type varchar              // Operation type: insert, delete, replace
  position int              // Position in content
  content text              // Operation content (if applicable)
  length int                // Length of deletion (for delete/replace)
  timestamp bigint          // Operation timestamp
  device_id varchar         // Device that originated the operation
  version int               // Version at time of operation
}

// History entries store version history for notes
Table history {
  id varchar [pk]           // History entry ID
  note_id varchar           // Note identifier
  room_id varchar [ref: > rooms.id]  // Reference to room
  content text              // Content snapshot (or delta)
  delta text                // Delta from previous version
  version int               // Version number
  timestamp bigint          // Creation timestamp
  device_name varchar       // Device name that created this version
  tags text                 // JSON array of tags
}

// Notebooks metadata (client-side storage, server doesn't store this)
// This is stored in client IndexedDB, not on server
Table notebooks_client {
  id varchar [pk]           // Notebook ID
  name varchar              // Notebook name
  mnemonic text             // Encrypted mnemonic
  encryption_key text       // Encrypted encryption key
  room_id varchar           // Associated room ID
  created_at bigint         // Creation timestamp
  updated_at bigint         // Last update timestamp
}

// Notes metadata (client-side storage)
Table notes_client {
  id varchar [pk]           // Note ID
  notebook_id varchar       // Parent notebook ID
  title varchar             // Note title
  tags text                 // JSON array of tags
  created_at bigint         // Creation timestamp
  updated_at bigint         // Last update timestamp
  version int               // Current version
}

// Offline operation queue (client-side storage)
Table offline_queue_client {
  id varchar [pk]           // Operation ID
  type varchar              // Operation type: update, create, delete
  notebook_id varchar       // Notebook ID
  note_id varchar           // Note ID (if applicable)
  data text                 // JSON operation data
  timestamp bigint          // Operation timestamp
  retries int               // Number of retry attempts
}

// Remote cursors for collaboration (transient, in-memory)
Table remote_cursors {
  id varchar [pk]           // Cursor ID
  room_id varchar [ref: > rooms.id]  // Reference to room
  device_id varchar         // Device ID
  device_name varchar       // Device display name
  color varchar             // Cursor color
  line int                  // Cursor line position
  column int                // Cursor column position
  selection_start text      // Selection start position (JSON)
  selection_end text        // Selection end position (JSON)
  timestamp bigint          // Last update timestamp
}
```

## Storage Backend Implementations

### Redis Schema

```
# Room storage (Hash)
room:{id} = {
  "encrypted_data": "...",
  "version": 42,
  "created_at": 1713369600000,
  "updated_at": 1713456000000,
  "expires_at": 1714060800000
}

# Operations log (List)
operations:{room_id} = [
  "{\"id\":\"op1\",\"type\":\"insert\",...}",
  "{\"id\":\"op2\",\"type\":\"delete\",...}"
]

# TTL for automatic cleanup
EXPIRE room:{id} 604800  # 7 days
```

### SQLite Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE rooms (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  created_at INTEGER NOT NULL,
  updated_at INTEGER NOT NULL,
  expires_at INTEGER NOT NULL,
  encrypted_data TEXT NOT NULL,
  version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
);

CREATE TABLE operations (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  room_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES rooms(id),
  type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(type IN ('insert', 'delete', 'replace')),
  position INTEGER NOT NULL,
  content TEXT,
  length INTEGER,
  timestamp INTEGER NOT NULL,
  device_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  version INTEGER NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE history (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  note_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  room_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES rooms(id),
  content TEXT,
  delta TEXT,
  version INTEGER NOT NULL,
  timestamp INTEGER NOT NULL,
  device_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  tags TEXT
);

-- Indexes for performance
CREATE INDEX idx_operations_room ON operations(room_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_operations_timestamp ON operations(timestamp);
CREATE INDEX idx_history_note ON history(note_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_history_room ON history(room_id);
```

## Data Retention Policy

| Data Type | Retention Period | Cleanup Method |
|-----------|------------------|----------------|
| Active rooms | 7 days after last update | Automatic TTL expiration |
| Operations log | 24 hours | Periodic cleanup job |
| History entries | 50 entries per note | FIFO eviction |
| Remote cursors | Session lifetime | In-memory, cleared on disconnect |

## Migration Strategy

When schema changes are required:
1. Create new migration file in `server/migrations/`
2. Apply migration during server startup
3. Support backward compatibility for one major version

